Yes, I saw that.

100
00:10:19,078 --> 00:10:22,123
Programmed behaviour,
prompted by suggestion -

101
00:10:22,207 --> 00:10:27,670
a rhythmic motion of the hands, producing
an unconscious act in a conscious state.

102
00:10:27,754 --> 00:10:29,881
Doesn't work on you.

103
00:10:30,048 --> 00:10:32,717
- I know what hypnosis is.
- Group hypnosis.

104
00:10:32,801 --> 00:10:35,762
If you're suggesting
Donnie escaped from prison

105
00:10:35,887 --> 00:10:39,849
using a technique from a Vegas
lounge act, I'd think again.

106
00:10:39,933 --> 00:10:42,977
Mesmer was able
to hypnotise entire audiences.

107
00:10:43,061 --> 00:10:45,897
So, how would Donnie
have acquired this ability?

108
00:10:46,022 --> 00:10:48,191
I'm not saying that it was Donnie.

109
00:10:48,274 --> 00:10:51,236
- Then who?
- Three inmates missing from three prisons.

110
00:10:51,361 --> 00:10:55,949
One man has had possible contact with
each of those cons. The prison chaplain.

111
00:10:56,074 --> 00:10:59,202
- "Glory. Amen."
