Centuries ago, in the Peruvian Andes, holy
men used to remove parts of their skulls

233
00:22:28,933 --> 00:22:32,520
to increase blood volume.
Or drill small holes.

234
00:22:32,603 --> 00:22:37,191
This hole in his head enables Reverend
Orison to help these prisoners escape?

235
00:22:37,274 --> 00:22:43,239
The practitioners of this found that
they could perform certain mental tricks.

236
00:22:43,322 --> 00:22:46,033
One of which they called
"stopping the world".

237
00:22:46,116 --> 00:22:49,453
Nobody can do that. I don't care
how many holes they have.

238
00:22:49,578 --> 00:22:51,622
But maybe they can alter perception,

239
00:22:51,705 --> 00:22:55,584
creating a disparate reality
which they project through hypnosis.

240
00:22:55,668 --> 00:22:58,420
But, why? I mean, even if he could, why?

241
00:22:58,504 --> 00:23:02,591
Donnie is serving a life sentence,
without possibility of parole.

242
00:23:02,675 --> 00:23:05,177
That's the final judgment of society.

243
00:23:05,261 --> 00:23:09,515
But not in the eyes of God. Or in the eyes
of a man who thinks he's God's tool.

244
00:23:09,598 --> 00:23:14,645
Well, if Reverend Orison meant to kill
Donnie Pf aster, then why is he still alive?

245
00:23:14,728 --> 00:23:17,898
Maybe he unleashed something
he couldn't control.

246
00:23:17,982 --> 00:23:20,901
Maybe he thought he was
opening the door of perception,

247
00:23:21,026 --> 00:23:26,073
but then, unwittingly, he...
opened the gates of hell.

248
00:23:28,867 --> 00:23:30,995
(beeping)

249
00:23:40,671 --> 00:23:43,757
- What?
- Glory. Amen.

250
00:23:44,091 --> 00:23:45,843
Glory. Amen.

251
00:23:45,926 --> 00:23:47,011
(beeping slows)

252
00:23:47,094 --> 00:23:49,597
Glory. Amen.

253
00:24:35,893 --> 00:24:38,562
(knock at door)

254
00:24:40,773 --> 00:24:43,400
- Are you Donald?
- Yes.

255
00:24:44,401 --> 00:24:47,613
I'm from Tip Top Gentlemen's Service.

256
00:24:59,583 --> 00:25:04,588
- This isn't your place, is it?
- No. Why?

257
00:25:04,672 --> 00:25:09,593
Cos I was coming up and got stopped by
the landlord, like it's any of his business.

258
00:25:09,677 --> 00:25:12,930
He told me some
Reverend Orison lives here.

259
00:25:13,013 --> 00:25:15,766
- Now, you ain't no preacher, are you?
- No.

260
00:25:15,891 --> 00:25:20,270
Good. They always like the weirdest things.

261
00:25:22,898 --> 00:25:25,317
You know what I mean?

262
00:25:41,041 --> 00:25:43,752
- You OK?
- Yes.

263
00:25:45,838 --> 00:25:48,632
Something you want to say?

264
00:25:51,385 --> 00:25:53,804
Love your hair.

265
00:26:15,951 --> 00:26:18,328
What are you doin'?

266
00:26:18,454 --> 00:26:22,166
- Is your hair chemically treated?
- My hair?

267
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:27,504
- I don't know which product to use.
- No, you're not using no product.

268
00:26:27,588 --> 00:26:31,592
My hair's clean. If you're gonna
be weird about it, I ought to leave.

269
00:26:31,675 --> 00:26:33,177
I'm being a gentleman.

270
00:26:33,260 --> 00:26:37,681
Well, be a gentleman and get me a towel.
I'm gonna get outta here.

271
00:27:02,289 --> 00:27:04,625
It's a wig.

272
00:27:06,919 --> 00:27:09,838
They lied to me.

273
00:27:10,756 --> 00:27:13,425
You lied to me!

274
00:27:29,399 --> 00:27:31,026
Where did he go?

275
00:27:31,109 --> 00:27:33,237
Marshal?

276
00:27:35,864 --> 00:27:38,492
- Marshal?
- What?

277
00:27:38,575 --> 00:27:42,329
The prisoner. The man you were guarding.
What happened to him?

278
00:27:42,412 --> 00:27:46,041
He's gone, Scully. So's the marshal's gun.

279
00:27:46,124 --> 00:27:48,335
You didn't see him?

280
00:27:51,797 --> 00:27:53,924
Let's go, Scully.

281
00:28:01,515 --> 00:28:04,518
- What is it?
- What does this mean?

282
00:28:09,064 --> 00:28:11,817
- Did you tell him?
- No, I only told you.

283
00:28:11,942 --> 00:28:15,863
He must have... overheard us
when we were talking in the hallway.

284
00:28:15,988 --> 00:28:18,824
- I didn't mention the name of the song.
- You did.

285
00:28:18,949 --> 00:28:21,368
No, I'm sure I didn't, Mulder.

286
00:28:21,451 --> 00:28:25,873
Well... maybe this was meant for you.

287
00:28:25,956 --> 00:28:28,333
"Don't look any further."

288
00:28:45,142 --> 00:28:47,227
(cocks gun)

289
00:28:49,688 --> 00:28:53,275
"Whosoever sheddeth man's blood...

290
00:28:53,358 --> 00:28:57,362
by man shall his blood be shed."

291
00:28:59,156 --> 00:29:01,992
- What are you doing?
- Taking you home.

292
00:29:06,163 --> 00:29:09,374
The wicked... will be punished.

293
00:29:23,263 --> 00:29:26,433
Pray for God's love, Donnie.

294
00:29:29,811 --> 00:29:33,440
Find the humility in yourself
to allow God into your heart.

295
00:29:33,523 --> 00:29:36,526
All you have to do is believe.

296
00:29:37,486 --> 00:29:42,658
Repent. You'll feel God's love come to show
you the way to his heavenly kingdom.

297
00:29:42,741 --> 00:29:44,451
(whimpers)

298
00:29:45,619 --> 00:29:51,458
- Are you sorry for what you've done?
- You... (mumbles)

299
00:29:51,541 --> 00:29:55,504
- What did you say?
- Never... no... no...

300
00:29:59,049 --> 00:30:03,178
- Why are you crying?
- I can't... I can't... (mumbles)

301
00:30:03,261 --> 00:30:05,889
Beg his forgiveness for what you did.

302
00:30:05,973 --> 00:30:09,977
For what you did to all
those poor, helpless girls.

303
00:30:10,060 --> 00:30:14,189
My violence is always waiting...
for an instant.

304
00:30:14,272 --> 00:30:16,900
For when his back is turned.

305
00:30:18,568 --> 00:30:20,112
You can see it now.

306
00:30:20,237 --> 00:30:24,491
Are you crying for your sins?
Or for yourself?

307
00:30:24,574 --> 00:30:28,996
No, Reverend. I cry for you...

308
00:30:29,871 --> 00:30:32,624
because you cannot kill me.

309
00:30:54,938 --> 00:30:58,442
You know, it's funny, when
all is said and done, there's...

310
00:30:58,525 --> 00:31:01,486
not much mystery in murder.

311
00:31:01,611 --> 00:31:04,489
And for that I owe you an apology, Mulder.

312
00:31:04,573 --> 00:31:06,867
What do you mean?

313
00:31:06,950 --> 00:31:11,872
Well, you were right. I was looking too hard
for connections that weren't there.

314
00:31:11,955 --> 00:31:15,042
Orison was a murderer, plain and simple.

315
00:31:15,125 --> 00:31:18,462
He liberated prisoners so he could
bring them here, pass judgment.

316
00:31:18,587 --> 00:31:22,883
I guess in his own twisted way
he was making good with his god.

317
00:31:22,966 --> 00:31:26,845
"Glory. Amen." Let's go home, Scully.

318
00:31:26,970 --> 00:31:31,433
You know, Donnie Pf aster placed the call
to the police that led us out here.

319
00:31:31,516 --> 00:31:33,977
It's like he's begging us to hunt him down.

320
00:31:34,102 --> 00:31:38,648
This X-file is over... lying dead there
in a grave he dug himself.

321
00:31:38,732 --> 00:31:41,860
Let's let the US Marshals
take over from here.

322
00:31:44,362 --> 00:31:47,157
Don't look any further, Scully.

323
00:33:59,331 --> 00:34:00,665
(phone rings)

324
00:34:00,749 --> 00:34:03,668
- Fox Mulder. Leave a message after the...
- (beep)

325
00:34:03,793 --> 00:34:06,213
Agent Mulder,
Marshal Joe Daddo in Marion.

326
00:34:06,296 --> 00:34:09,633
Just talked to a call girl
who lD'd Donnie as an attacker.

327
00:34:09,758 --> 00:34:12,928
Claims Pf aster got upset
when she was wearing a red wig.

328
00:34:13,053 --> 00:34:18,058
Upset she wasn't a redhead. This mean
anything to you? Appreciate a call back.

329
00:34:41,331 --> 00:34:42,499
(yells)

330
00:35:28,628 --> 00:35:30,922
Go back to hell!

331
00:35:34,801 --> 00:35:37,971
- Who does your nails, girly girl?
- Let me go!

332
00:35:38,054 --> 00:35:41,474
The only reason you're alive
is because I asked the judge for life!

333
00:35:41,558 --> 00:35:45,186
The only reason is because
we didn't kill you when we could!

334
00:35:45,270 --> 00:35:47,314
You're the one that got away.

335
00:35:49,274 --> 00:35:52,527
- You're all I think about.
- I'm a federal agent.

336
00:35:52,610 --> 00:35:56,614
You do anything to me and they
will not give you a break this time.

337
00:35:56,698 --> 00:35:58,325
I'm going to run you a bath.

338
00:35:58,408 --> 00:35:59,534
(screams)

339
00:36:11,755 --> 00:36:13,506
("Don't Look Any Further")

340
00:36:13,590 --> 00:36:15,717
(turns radio off)

341
00:36:16,968 --> 00:36:19,429
(turns radio on)

342
00:36:19,512 --> 00:36:23,016
("Don't Look Any Further" by John Hiatt)

343
00:36:41,785 --> 00:36:46,289
Now be good, and don't
cause me any problems.

344
00:36:54,798 --> 00:36:56,925
(water running)

345
00:36:58,218 --> 00:37:01,304
(phone ringing)

346
00:37:04,599 --> 00:37:07,894
(continues ringing)

347
00:37:14,275 --> 00:37:17,946
("Don't Look Any Further"
by John Hiatt)

348
00:37:19,239 --> 00:37:21,324
(ringing tone)

349
00:40:08,408 --> 00:40:10,493
(turns stereo off)

350
00:40:48,448 --> 00:40:52,410
(mouthing) Put 'em up!

351
00:41:19,812 --> 00:41:22,148
(mouthing) Did he hurt you?

352
00:42:06,943 --> 00:42:08,986
(door opens)

353
00:42:12,407 --> 00:42:15,451
- Excuse me.
- (cop) Yeah. Sure.

354
00:42:26,295 --> 00:42:30,049
If you want to pack some things,
we can get out of here.

355
00:42:30,133 --> 00:42:32,218
Yeah.

356
00:42:39,934 --> 00:42:42,437
You can't judge yourself.

357
00:42:48,818 --> 00:42:52,864
- Maybe I don't have to.
- The Bible allows for vengeance.

358
00:42:53,740 --> 00:42:55,992
But the law doesn't.

359
00:42:57,243 --> 00:43:00,705
The way I see it...
he didn't give you a choice.

360
00:43:02,790 --> 00:43:08,004
And my report will reflect that...
in case you're worried.

361
00:43:08,129 --> 00:43:12,592
Donnie Pf aster would have surely
killed again if given the chance.

362
00:43:12,675 --> 00:43:14,969
He was evil, Mulder.

363
00:43:15,887 --> 00:43:20,767
I'm sure about that without a doubt.
But there's one thing that I'm not sure of.

364
00:43:22,185 --> 00:43:25,813
- What's that?
- Who was at work in me?

365
00:43:27,482 --> 00:43:30,443
Or what?

366
00:43:30,526 --> 00:43:34,155
What made me...

367
00:43:34,238 --> 00:43:37,033
What made me pull the trigger?

368
00:43:37,658 --> 00:43:40,286
You mean, if it was God?

369
00:43:40,369 --> 00:43:43,664
I mean... what if it wasn't?

370
00:44:28,626 --> 00:44:31,629
Visiontext Subtitles: Yasmin Rammohan

371
00:44:31,712 --> 00:44:33,256
(Child) I made this!

